comment: Animals are exploited by us at an alarming rate. For anything and everything. If you have ever tried to be vegan, you know that dairy and other animal products are found in just about every processed food, and it is absolutely ridiculous! People don't understand that when they eat that burger or box of chicken nuggets--or even ice cream cone--that they are contributing towards mass torture and murder. Animals want to live just like we do. We have no right to take away their freedom or their lives. And for what?! For something we don't need at all. For something that passes over our tongue in an instant and is gone. For something that causes all kinds of long-term health issues and contributes to worldwide obesity. I've been vegetarian for several years and vegan for about a year, and I've never felt better. I feel like I'm being true to my beliefs and convictions and my body feels healthier and stronger than ever. I wish more people understood the hell they are perpetuating for animals when they continue to live their lives in ignorance. The world needs more empathy.  (created at:2014-03-27 12:41:24)
